The folder 'pencil-code/config/hosts' contains templates for local 
configuration files using the new configuration method presented in the 
manual. Please indicate for what machine your configuration is 
implemeted.  

Examples:

ajohan   -  GNU_Linux-Ubuntu, MacBook Pro
dhruba   -  GNU_Linux-Ubuntu ?
mps      -  GNU_Linux-Ubuntu ?
piyali   -  Dell GNU_Linux 
sintef   -  Dell GNU_Linux
Toulouse -  LATT/LMTG cluster, 8 core Linux
andreas  -  Configuration for condor queing program
kis      -  Suse Linux MPI cluster
kis      -  Sun Solaris with shared memory and MPI
mps      -  GNU_Linux-Ubuntu desktops
nordita  -  Pencil Code server
RZG      -
sven     -  GNU_Linux-Ubuntu
wdobler  -
wlyra    - GNU/Linux - Ubuntu, Suse

Andreas Svedin 2010
